cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
authors:
  - family-names: Fu
    given-names: Hai Hai
title: "When Correctness, Robustness, and Stability Coincide: A Unified Framework via Degrees of Freedom and Structural Collapse"
version: "0.2"
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.19871473
date-released: "2026-04-29"
url: "https://github.com/minustwo/canonical-reality-theory"
license: CC-BY-4.0
abstract: >
  Canonical Reality Theory (CRT) is a structural theory of when correctness,
  robustness, and stability coincide. Using a minimal language based on states,
  rule closure, break structures, and system dynamics, we show that these
  notions coincide precisely when all degrees of freedom vanish: DoF(P)=(0,0,0).
  The synthesis theorem characterizes this as a structural collapse. For open
  systems, the execution layer determines the minimum control-plane vulnerability.
keywords:
  - canonical reality
  - degrees of freedom
  - structural collapse
  - correctness
  - robustness
  - stability
  - DeFi
  - min-cut
  - stochastic stability
